commit.message: Support latest setuptools which does not support use_2to3.

htail: Fix support for python3.

response.read returns bytes, so some encoding detection and decoding have
to happen.

htail: Ignore existing .netrc if -n/--netrc is not provided.

As originally intended.

htail: Use "except ... as ..." instead of "except ..., ...".

This is supported since 2.6, and reduces differences from 2to3.

Don't display body when status is REQUESTED_RANGE_NOT_SATISFIABLE

The body data may be an error message which is not part of the
file being tailed, and therefore not useful to see.
htail: EPIPE (connection closed by peer) is also a temporary failure.
Fix URLs not being retried when initial seek fails and "retry" is true.
HTTPFile: Implement "tell" and get a nicer repr.
Use standard constant names for seek's "whence" argument.
Skip URLs for which HEAD call does not return a "good" status.

Do not drop URL on bad status line error.

Also, do not drop URL on httplib state inconsistency.
Treat ECONNRESET the same way as EHOSTUNREACH.
Handle socket EHOSTUNREACH errors as temporary errors.
